<item>
            <title>[LU-20084] osp: fix kobject leak when LWP connect fails</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20084</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;lwp_setup()&lt;/b&gt; calls &lt;b&gt;client_obd_setup()&lt;/b&gt; which creates the LDLM namespace via &lt;b&gt;ldlm_namespace_new()&lt;/b&gt;. When &lt;b&gt;lwp_obd_connect()&lt;/b&gt; subsequently fails, the out_dis error path calls &lt;b&gt;class_disconnect()&lt;/b&gt; without first calling &lt;b&gt;ldlm_namespace_free_prior()&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This leaves &lt;b&gt;LDLM_NS_STOPPING&lt;/b&gt; unset, so when &lt;b&gt;client_obd_cleanup()&lt;/b&gt; later calls &lt;b&gt;ldlm_namespace_free_post()&lt;/b&gt;, the pool recalc race can cause &lt;b&gt;ldlm_namespace_sysfs_unregister()&lt;/b&gt; to hang and the namespace&#160;kobject to be leaked under /sys/fs/lustre/ldlm/namespaces/.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Same pattern as &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20079&quot; title=&quot;ldlm: kobject leak when client connect fails before obd_connect completes&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-20079&quot;&gt;LU-20079&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; in &lt;b&gt;client_connect_import()&lt;/b&gt;, but in &lt;b&gt;lwp_obd_connect()&lt;/b&gt; &#8212; triggered by MDT mount failures rather than client mount failures.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
